title: Wall Street Breakfast June 8: Consumer Credit Expands More Than Expected, Consumer Spending Remains Strong
author: Seeking Alpha
dc:creator: Seeking Alpha
description: US reportedly seeking funds to purchase enriched uranium. Consumer credit expands more than expected in April. Consumer spending remains strong as pendulum swings to services, Visa CFO says. Deeper dive: Is the current inflation situation comparable to the 1970s? Catch today’s WSB article here.
